		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Sun, Feb 13th 6:41 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=110832765395582215&num=73&page=1&post=1&replyto=110833807957936585"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=384524"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=110833807957936585></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=384524"><span id=Scholar>Teleos</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />295 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.58]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Teleos&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ahh good stuff. I agree with your overall approach. Things are different IN GUILD groups though. I would always do CAWU (NBG) for guild friends. If you have a mixed group (four guild and two friends) you need to be very clear up front.<br><br>In general, the critical issues is knowing and saying what the loot rules are. For instance, I have not felt great coming into a group where one person is main looting (with the groups concensus). I do my bit, say I need to leave after a while... and guess what... the ML makes no comment, does not offer to go and sell... so no plat for me. <br><br>The other problem with main looting and then selling and splitting in zones you don't know much about is that loot that could have fetched a pretty penny in the Bazaar gets flogged off to a vendor. The main looter I respect would know the realistic value and use for items, and would actively balance drops, bazaar items and vendor trash for the group. They would also have a plan for how to sell (some zones are a long way from a vendor). <br><br>I get concerned about AFK issues and xp. &quot;Hey need a quick afk phone ringing&quot; is fine.. one pull later they are back and all is well. &quot;Hey going afk for 5 minutes, gonna sit out of the zone&quot; is ok too. &quot;sorry guys Auntie Gwen is here I'll be back in ten minutes&quot; ... then sit on butt in camp? No thanks, that gets you booted. Do it as LEADER??? Seen that, and we all jumped out and regrouped. In addition in many camps the danger of a train wiping you out (or worse group dies trying to defend your worthless bod). <br><br>There are etiquette issues if you are a buffing class. <br>1) If folk ask for buffs while you are fighting, refuse. Consider their case later.<br>2) If folk ask for buffs but your group is waiting on you to med up b efore pulling, refuse and explain the situation. <br>3) If you have plenty of manna, tell the group and go for it.<br>4) if it is an exchange for a buff the group wants, go for it. <br>I personally NEVER accept donations for buffs when on the killing fields. <br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Hack that mob to bits.. get it down to ones and zeros fast!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
