		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=384524"><span id=Scholar>Teleos</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />295 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.58]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Teleos&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>NGB is Need Before Greed (also CAWU Can and Will Use). <br><br>These both denote the idea that if a nice piece of loot drops the loot is offered first to someone in the group who can actually use it (as opposed to sell it). Typically this means the group leader or main looter will link the item to everyone and ask &quot;who CAWU?&quot;. To say yes means the character currently playing should be able to equip the item, and it should be better than the item currently worn or equipped. Sometimes the player will say &quot;yes please that is better than link_the_current_item&quot;. <br><br>Saying &quot;I need that for my alt&quot; does not really count as CAWU. We all have alts.. and we all MIGHT decide to sell it afterall. <br><br>FFA means &quot;free for all&quot;. Thus everyone or everyone who chooses too can put up their hand. The easiest way in a group is then to &quot;alpha roll&quot;. If four people say &quot;in&quot; then /rand 1 4. Use this to count down the names in alphabeticall order. If the random number is three, then Billystiger and Guthacker miss out, and Gwendoline wins. Xaviour misses out too. <br><br>NONE of this applies to No Drop items, as they OBVIOUSLY should only be picked up by folk who can use them. They cannot be swapped to your alt. <br><br>With atuneable items around now, you can CAWU and prove it. Pick it up, equip it (not augs of course, no bird bath around) then link it. It will show &quot;No Drop&quot; now. </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Hack that mob to bits.. get it down to ones and zeros fast!</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
