		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Mar 1st 11:05 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=110832765395582215&num=73&page=1&post=1&replyto=110973653855742171"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=110973653855742171></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9795 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.03]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">Namblak wrote:</b><hr size="1" />Agree whole heartedly on the /random occasionally picking on me. <br><br>If it wasn't for someone in the group who won like three rolls and giving me one before we split it would have been a long slow day for loot.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Heh. You've got some greedy groups then. In most groups people will only roll on *one* piece of major loot until everyone has gotten something. I suppose this varies from area to area, but for example in OoW zones, it's pretty standard to be eligible for only one rune, one quest piece, and one &quot;greed&quot; loot piece, until everyone has gotten one. So while I suppose it's technically possible for a group to get just one of each and for one person to get all three, that really doesn't happen very often.<br><br>And those are special rules because there really are three distinct types of loot availiable in those zones. Anywhere else, we'd only roll on valuable loot until you got one, then pass until everyone else got one, then maybe start over. You have to kinda play it by ear obviously, but I've never seen there be too much trouble with the basic idea. People generally have an idea of the relative value of things that drop in an area. So everyone rolls on the &quot;common&quot; junk items if they want them, but a valuable &quot;rare&quot; would be a separate category (and open for all to roll on again).<br><br><br>It's not a perfect system, but it's what I've seen most pickup groups use, and it tends to work pretty well. I've also found that folks tend to stick at those camps for long periods of time though, so that may explain why it works. It's not uncommon to walk out of a OoW zone session with 30-40k worth of loot and a few runes (and about 6+ hours of really solid exp under your belt).</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
