		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.57]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I agree mostly with Czae, but one of the cool things about the OoW camps that Gbaji is talking about is, because most of the loot is lore and attuneable. It being lore, they can't have more then one, obviously. But because it's attuneable, most of it isn't tributeable either (some of it is guild tributeable, but most of it isn't). Of course, people could pass it on to their alts, but you only have so many alts that can hold this crap. I'm talking about stuff like the Silken Turban of Serfdom and other very common drops, not the Bloodstones of the dance and EoEs. Those very rarely, if ever, will go to CAWU or NBG, because they're so rare (well, maybe the EoE would still).</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></t