		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=392902"><span id=>Ldder</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />15 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Ldder&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I've always thought NBG was a good and friendly way to go but i have never understood why someone who wins the roll dont link the stuff they will replace so everyone gets to roll on the &quot;lesser&quot; stuff and maybe sell it for some plat.<br><br>On the other hand, everything that is not no drop is just plat so everyone should roll. Even a rune is just cash since you can trade it. So what you really roll for on a rune is 15k. NBG here would be what?</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />56 wizzy on Tunare server<br>&lt;Fellowship of the unbroken&gt;</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
