		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=468881"><span id=Scholar>BellamDreamguard</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="71" src="/uf/BellamDreamguard/Velma.JPG"><br /><br />46 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=BellamDreamguard&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I personally don't find /Random to be any more fair than CAWU, only more arbitrary.<br><br>Furthermore, I see each person that I group with as someone I might group with again, until they prove differently. As a decently equiped lvl 51 paladin, who doesn't have a guild, the times I get to roll on a CAWU item are extremely few and far between. I don't adhere to CAWU because I'm greedy, I do it because I think it's the right thing to do.<br><br>When I form a group, I usually state my prefference for CAWU. If noone objects in the initial group, CAWU is announced each time we pick up a player, right along with who the puller, tank and looter are, and anything else vital that needs to be communicated. If people don't like it, they can suggest we switch, or find another group.<br><br>It's really not that hard, as long as expectations are clearly communicated up front.<br><br>Then again, the game is probably different up there at 65+ than it is down here at 51.<br><br>- Oh, I should probably point out that I have no problem staying in a non-CAWU group, as long as looting rules were stated at the onset. I've been shorted my fair share of the time.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar&nbsp;&nbsp;3 21:43:21 2005 by BellamDreamguard</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Bellam Dreamguard<br>Cavalier of Thunder<br>Qeynos Chapter<br>-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-<br> Cazic Thule <br><br><br>"LORD, WHAT CAN THE HARVEST HOPE FOR, IF NOT FOR THE CARE OF THE REAPER MAN?"<br><br> -Terry Pratchett</td></td></tr