		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.56]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=czaemon&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />I personally don't find /Random to be any more fair than CAWU, only more arbitrary.<br><br>Furthermore, I see each person that I group with as someone I might group with again, until they prove differently. As a decently equiped lvl 51 paladin, who doesn't have a guild, the times I get to roll on a CAWU item are extremely few and far between. I don't adhere to CAWU because I'm greedy, I do it because I think it's the right thing to do.<br><br>When I form a group, I usually state my prefference for CAWU. If noone objects in the initial group, CAWU is announced each time we pick up a player, right along with who the puller, tank and looter are, and anything else vital that needs to be communicated. If people don't like it, they can suggest we switch, or find another group.<br><br>It's really not that hard, as long as expectations are clearly communicated up front.<br><br>Then again, the game is probably different up there at 65+ than it is down here at 5<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>in pickup groups, even honest cawu is inherently flawed.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>In a six person group:<br>1) 15k buffed warrior<br>2) 10k buffed monk<br>3) 10k buffed ranger<br>4) 10k buffed cleric<br>5) 15k buffed warrior<br>6) 6k buffed monk<br><br>the monk will be able to cawu more than anyone else.  Yet, he will be contributing the least.  The other people's chance at loot is actually damaged by inviting a lower geared character, they could do much better in a cawu group by just waiting for another geared person goes lfg.<br><br>also:<br>person 6 wins boots b in zone c.  boots b are a 25hp upgrade to boots d, his previous boots.  I don't think anyone can argue that 25hp is too slight to call cawu on.. but let's assume his old boots, boots d, are droppable, and worth 40k platinum.<br><br>Person 6, who is contributing the least to his group walks out not only with a 25hp upgrade, but with 40,000 platinum. </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.czaemon.com" target="akztarg">Czaemon</a><br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from I'M IN UR BASE, KILLING UR DOODZ!</td></tr></table>
