		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 3rd 10:17 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=110832765395582215&num=73&page=1&post=1&replyto=110990619914809396"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=110990619914809396></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1286"><span id=Encyclopedia>gbaji</span></a><b><span id=Encyclopedia><br>Encyclopedia</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />9795 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.68]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Of course Czae. Which is why I said that a CAWU system with rotated drops (each can only get one drop of a particular value range until everyone has gotten one) works well.<br><br>Let's take that same group then. They are at a WoS camp. For persons 1-5 there is nothing that drops at the camp that they'd actually use. For person 6, there's several possible drops that may be upgrades for him (and many more that wont due to class restrictions, right?).<br><br>Those boots drop and are a 25hp upgrade to him. He says he can and will use them. The rest of the group agrees, and he gets them. Then another item that he can't use drops, and the other 5 roll on it. Then another item drop and the remaining 4 roll on it. Then a pair of gloves drop that he can use and would actually be a 30hp upgrade for him. Gee. He'd like to have them, but he's ineligible since he already got his upgrade. Now, if the other three want to let him trade his boots for the bracer, that's up to them, but in any case, he only gets one piece...<br><br><br>In addition to that, all the runes are rolled on separately, so are not taken into consideration.<br><br>That's the system I'm talking about, and it works particularly well. If we went with straight random rolls instead of allowing CAWU to have some effect, then it's entirely possible that person 3 will get an item that person 6 could have used, but he's just going to tribute it, meanwhile, person 6 is stuck with the item he got via random chance, and it's something he can't use. He now can either sell it and hope to buy something useful with the cash, or tribute it and just hope to get a useful drop next time.<br><br><br>As I said earlier, you can look at it like trading items. If you've got two items of similar tribute or resale value, and one person CAWU one and you don't care, why not let that guy have the item he can use and you keep the other one? In a camp with a sufficient rate of drops, this works just fine. Obviously, if you're at a camp with only rare and valuable drops (like one thing of value will drop during the entire time you are there), then CAWU is meaningless. It only applies when item drops are going to occur frequently enough to even out across the group as a way to more efficiently distribute them.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
