		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.68]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Oh. And just to flip the other side of the coin, CAWU absolutely does *not* work in camps where the only drops are for particular classes.<br><br>See... the problem with your post about your pally and prefering CAWU loot rules is that as a player you have quite a bit of choice as to what camps you go to. So you can certainly go looking for groups in zones and camps where you know items drop for your class. Gee. Isn't that convenient that there's a nice weapon that drops here that is shd/pal only? Good thing we decided that we're using CAWU system...<br><br><br>I've seen the system definately abused in the past, and in many camps of old it simply could not work at all. Just try getting a healer to join your group at a camp where CAWU has been called and the only valuable drop there is an int caster item. It just doesn't work.<br><br><br>I'm also surprised you take this position with a paladin. Trust me. You're screwing yourself in the long run. Leather wearers gain the most from CAWU from what I've seen. There are lots of leather drops that seem to pop up off trash mobs in lower end zones in most of the last few expansions. Next most common trash and/or single group loots are cloth, followed by chain, and then finally (and this is so rare as to be stupid really) plate.<br><br><br>I'd seriously rethink your insistence on CAWU with your pally. I can tell you right now that you'll get virtually zero drops that way. Sure, you'll get the occasional knight only weapon or shield, but other then that... nothing. All the &quot;newer&quot; expansion are geared that way. PoP, GoD, and OoW have virtually zero plate armor bits available that you don't have to raid for, so your best bet for gear upgrades in your 50s and early 60s is to get cash drops off random rolls in hunting zones and *buying* gear.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
